<p>
	Wild yam tincture is the result of extracting the active ingredient of the pure herb using alcohol and water. Alcohol is the most popular extractant for use with wild yam and helps give it a longer shelf-life. Wild yam has a wide range of uses but is best known as a treatment for P.M.T. hot flushes, menopause and cramps etc. It can relax muscles and relieve pain. Also used for rheumatoid arthritis it is becoming a very popular oil. Herb:Alcohol ratio =&nbsp;1:3.</p>
